      {id:"ji2",title:"PID Control",est:"25 min",content:`## What is PID?
PID is a feedback control algorithm that makes your robot reach a target accurately and smoothly.

## The Three Terms
- P (Proportional) -- Output proportional to current error
- I (Integral) -- Sums error over time; fixes persistent offset
- D (Derivative) -- Rate of change of error; prevents overshoot

\`\`\`
output = (kP x error) + (kI x integral) + (kD x derivative)
\`\`\`

## Java Implementation -- Heading Control
\`\`\`java
double kP = 0.01, kI = 0.0001, kD = 0.005;
double integral = 0, lastError = 0;
double targetAngle = 90.0;

while (opModeIsActive()) {
    double error = targetAngle - imu.getHeading();
    while (error > 180)  error -= 360;
    while (error < -180) error += 360;

    integral  += error * 0.02;
    double derivative = (error - lastError) / 0.02;
    double output = kP*error + kI*integral + kD*derivative;

    leftMotor.setPower(basePower + output);
    rightMotor.setPower(basePower - output);
    lastError = error;
    sleep(20);
}
\`\`\`

## Tuning Steps
1. kI = kD = 0. Increase kP until oscillating
2. Add kD to damp oscillation (try kP/10)
3. Add small kI only if there is steady-state error`},
