Each swerve module has:
- Drive motor: spins the wheel for propulsion
- Steer motor: rotates the wheel direction (0-360 degrees)
- Absolute encoder: knows wheel angle at startup (usually CANCoder or MA3)
- Gear stages: ~6-7:1 steering, ~6-8:1 driving typical

