      {id:"mb8",title:"Fasteners & Thread Locking",est:"11 min",content:`## Fasteners: Small Parts, Big Consequences
Loose bolts cause more robot failures than broken motors. Knowing fasteners is a core build skill.

## Types in FTC/FRC
- **Socket Head Cap Screw (SHCS)**: most common, hex driver
- **Button Head**: low-profile, same hex driver
- **Set Screw**: locks shaft collars — must use Loctite
- **Standoff**: creates precise spacing between plates
- **Rivet**: permanent, fast, blind fastening

## Thread Engagement Rule
Bolt should engage at least **1× its diameter** in threads.
M3 bolt → 3mm minimum thread depth in aluminum
Under-engaged threads strip under shock loads.

## Loctite Guide
| Color | Strength | When to Use |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| Blue 243 | Removable | All structural bolts, mechanism pivots |
| Red 271 | Permanent | Bolts you'll never remove |
| None | — | Bolts removed frequently (battery, inspection panels) |

⚠️ Never Loctite into plastic — it dissolves the threads.

## Anti-Vibration Tricks
- Use Loctite + proper torque (don't over-tighten)
- Nylock nuts on high-vibration pivot points
- Split lock washers on motor mounts
- Thread inserts (Helicoil) for aluminum you remove often`},
