      {id:"wb5",title:"CSS Grid Layout",est:"13 min",content:`## CSS Grid: Two-Dimensional Layout
Flexbox is one-dimensional (row OR column). Grid is two-dimensional (rows AND columns simultaneously). Perfect for dashboards and match displays.

\`\`\`css
/* 3-column responsive dashboard */
.dashboard {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); /* 3 equal columns */
  gap: 16px;
  padding: 20px;
}

/* Specific template */
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr; /* sidebar + main */
  grid-template-rows: 60px 1fr 40px; /* header + content + footer */
  height: 100vh;
}
.sidebar { grid-column: 1; grid-row: 1 / 3; }
.header  { grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1; }
.main    { grid-column: 2; grid-row: 2; }
.footer  { grid-column: 1 / 3; grid-row: 3; }
\`\`\`

## Auto-Fit Responsive Grid (Most Useful)
\`\`\`css
.team-cards {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 12px;
}
/* Cards are automatically 280px+ wide, wrap to next row as needed */
/* No media queries needed! */
\`\`\`

## Grid vs Flexbox: When to Use Each
- **Flexbox**: nav bars, button groups, centering single items
- **Grid**: page layouts, card grids, any 2D arrangement`},

      {id:"wb6",title:"JavaScript DOM Events",est:"14 min",content:`## Events Make Pages Interactive
Every click, keypress, scroll, and form input fires an event. You listen for events to run your code.

\`\`\`javascript
// Click events
button.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
  console.log("Clicked!", event.target);
});

// Keyboard events
document.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
  if (e.key === "Enter") submitForm();
  if (e.ctrlKey && e.key === "s") saveData();
});

// Input events (fires on every keystroke)
searchInput.addEventListener("input", (e) => {
  filterTeams(e.target.value);
});

// Form submission (prevent default refresh)
form.addEventListener("submit", (e) => {
  e.preventDefault(); // IMPORTANT: stops page reload
  const data = new FormData(form);
  saveScoutData(Object.fromEntries(data));
});
\`\`\`

## Event Delegation (One Listener for Many Elements)
\`\`\`javascript
// BAD: adds listener to every card
cards.forEach(card => card.addEventListener("click", handler));

// GOOD: one listener on parent, check which child was clicked
teamList.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
  const card = e.target.closest(".team-card");
  if (card) selectTeam(card.dataset.teamNumber);
});
\`\`\``},
