      {id:"wi4",title:"TypeScript Basics",est:"17 min",content:`## Why TypeScript?
TypeScript adds types to JavaScript. It catches bugs before you run the code — huge in production scouting apps.

\`\`\`typescript
// JavaScript — no safety
function getScore(team) {
  return team.auto + team.teleop; // team could be anything!
}

// TypeScript — compiler catches mistakes
interface TeamData {
  number: number;
  name: string;
  auto: number;
  teleop: number;
  reliability?: number; // ? means optional
}

function getScore(team: TeamData): number {
  return team.auto + team.teleop; // IDE helps you here
}
\`\`\`

## Type Annotations
\`\`\`typescript
// Variables
let teamNumber: number = 1234;
let teamName: string = "Gear Grinders";
let isEliminated: boolean = false;
let scores: number[] = [45, 52, 61, 38];

// Functions
function average(nums: number[]): number {
  return nums.reduce((a, b) => a + b) / nums.length;
}

// Generics
function first<T>(arr: T[]): T | undefined {
  return arr[0];
}
const topTeam = first<TeamData>(rankedTeams);
\`\`\`

## React + TypeScript
\`\`\`tsx
interface TeamCardProps {
  team: TeamData;
  onSelect: (number: number) => void;
}
function TeamCard({ team, onSelect }: TeamCardProps) {
  return <div onClick={() => onSelect(team.number)}>{team.name}</div>;
}
\`\`\``},

      {id:"wi5",title:"Local Storage & IndexedDB",est:"15 min",content:`## Persisting Data in the Browser
Scouting apps need to save data even when offline. The browser has two storage options.

## localStorage — Simple Key/Value
\`\`\`javascript
// Save
localStorage.setItem("scoutData", JSON.stringify(scoutEntries));

// Load
const raw = localStorage.getItem("scoutData");
const entries = raw ? JSON.parse(raw) : [];

// Delete
localStorage.removeItem("scoutData");
localStorage.clear(); // nuclear option

// Limits: ~5MB, strings only, synchronous
\`\`\`

## When localStorage Isn't Enough
For large datasets (1000+ scouting entries), use IndexedDB.

\`\`\`javascript
// Using the idb library (much simpler API)
import { openDB } from "idb";

const db = await openDB("scoutApp", 1, {
  upgrade(db) {
    db.createObjectStore("entries", { keyPath: "id", autoIncrement: true });
  }
});

// Add entry
await db.add("entries", { team: 1234, match: 5, auto: 15, teleop: 32 });

// Get all entries
const all = await db.getAll("entries");

// Query by team
const tx = db.transaction("entries");
// (use IDB cursor for filtering)
\`\`\`

## Offline Sync Strategy
1. Save all scout entries to IndexedDB immediately
2. When online: batch-sync to Firebase/Supabase
3. Show sync status indicator in UI`},
