      {id:"ji14",title:"PID Control Deep Dive",est:"28 min",content:`## PID Controllers

PID makes motors go exactly where you want — it's the most important control algorithm in robotics.

### The PID Formula
\`\`\`
output = (Kp × error) + (Ki × integral) + (Kd × derivative)
\`\`\`

| Term | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| P (Proportional) | Power proportional to error |
| I (Integral) | Fixes steady offset P alone can't fix |
| D (Derivative) | Damps oscillation |

### Simple P Controller
\`\`\`java
double Kp = 0.005;
double target = 1000; // encoder ticks

public void loop() {
    double error = target - motor.getCurrentPosition();
    double power = Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, Kp * error));
    motor.setPower(power);
}
\`\`\`

### Tuning Steps
1. Start with Kp only (Ki=Kd=0)
2. Raise Kp until it oscillates
3. Back off Kp 30%
4. Add Kd slowly to reduce bounce
5. Add Ki only if there's a steady offset
