      {id:"ji16",title:"Encoders and Precise Movement",est:"25 min",content:`## Encoder-Based Driving

Encoders measure exactly how far your motors have turned, enabling precise autonomous movement.

### What is an Encoder?
A small sensor attached to the motor shaft that counts electrical pulses as it rotates. More ticks = more rotation.

\`\`\`
Typical FTC motor: 537.7 ticks per revolution (goBILDA 5202)
If wheel diameter = 4 inches:
  Circumference = π × 4 = 12.57 inches
  Ticks per inch = 537.7 / 12.57 = 42.8 ticks/inch
\`\`\`

### Setting Up Encoders
\`\`\`java
// In init():
motor.setMode(DcMotor.RunMode.STOP_AND_RESET_ENCODER);
motor.setMode(DcMotor.RunMode.RUN_USING_ENCODER);
\`\`\`

### Drive a Specific Distance
\`\`\`java
public void driveInches(double inches, double power) {
    int ticks = (int)(inches * TICKS_PER_INCH); // e.g. 42.8

    leftDrive.setTargetPosition(leftDrive.getCurrentPosition() + ticks);
    rightDrive.setTargetPosition(rightDrive.getCurrentPosition() + ticks);

    leftDrive.setMode(DcMotor.RunMode.RUN_TO_POSITION);
    rightDrive.setMode(DcMotor.RunMode.RUN_TO_POSITION);

    leftDrive.setPower(power);
    rightDrive.setPower(power);

    while (leftDrive.isBusy() && rightDrive.isBusy() && opModeIsActive()) {
        telemetry.addData("Left ticks", leftDrive.getCurrentPosition());
        telemetry.addData("Right ticks", rightDrive.getCurrentPosition());
        telemetry.update();
    }

    leftDrive.setPower(0);
    rightDrive.setPower(0);
    leftDrive.setMode(DcMotor.RunMode.RUN_USING_ENCODER);
    rightDrive.setMode(DcMotor.RunMode.RUN_USING_ENCODER);
}
