      {id:"ei8",title:"Servo Control and PWM Signals",est:"20 min",content:`## Servos and PWM

Servos are motors with built-in position control. They're used for claws, arms, hoods, and anything needing precise position.

### Standard Servo vs Continuous Rotation
| Type | setPosition() | What Happens |
|------|---------------|-------------|
| Standard | 0.0 – 1.0 | Moves to angle (0° – 180°) |
| Continuous | 0.0 – 1.0 | Controls SPEED (0.5 = stop) |
