      {id:"ja14",title:"Road Runner 1.0 — Trajectories",est:"35 min",content:`## Road Runner 1.0 — Modern FTC Pathing

Road Runner 1.0 (not legacy 0.5) uses a different API that's cleaner and more powerful.

### Setup in MecanumDrive
\`\`\`java
// Road Runner 1.0 uses a different pose representation
// Pose2d uses (x, y, heading) in inches and radians
Pose2d startPose = new Pose2d(0, 0, Math.toRadians(0));
MecanumDrive drive = new MecanumDrive(hardwareMap, startPose);
\`\`\`

### Building a Trajectory Action
\`\`\`java
// Trajectories are built as "Action" objects (RR 1.0)
Action trajectoryAction = drive.actionBuilder(startPose)
    .lineToX(24)           // Move 24" in current direction
    .waitSeconds(0.5)
    .lineToY(12)
    .turn(Math.toRadians(-90))
    .splineTo(new Vector2d(48, -12), Math.toRadians(0))
    .build();
\`\`\`

### Running Actions
\`\`\`java
// Actions run as a linear sequence
@Override
public void runOpMode() {
    MecanumDrive drive = new MecanumDrive(hardwareMap, startPose);

    Action auto = drive.actionBuilder(startPose)
        .lineToX(24)
        .build();

    waitForStart();

    // Run the action — blocks until complete
    Actions.runBlocking(auto);
}
\`\`\`

### Sequential + Parallel Actions
\`\`\`java
// SequentialAction: runs one after another
// ParallelAction: runs simultaneously
Action auto = new SequentialAction(
    drive.actionBuilder(startPose).lineToX(24).build(),
    new ParallelAction(
        arm.raiseAction(),           // Arm goes up
        drive.actionBuilder(...)     // While driving next segment
            .lineToY(12)
            .build()
    ),
    new InstantAction(() -> intake.setPower(-1))
);
