      {id:"mi13",title:"Linear Slides — Design and Build",est:"25 min",content:`## Linear Slides for Vertical Extension

Linear slides let your robot reach far beyond its frame — essential for high-goal scoring and hanging.

### Slide Types
**V-Rail / C-Channel Cascade:**
- Each stage extends as the previous reaches limit
- Single motor can extend multiple stages (cascade)
- Used by: goBILDA, REV, Misumi

**Drawer Slides:**
- Commercial or custom
- Smooth, low friction
- Good load capacity

**Belt/String Cascade:**
- String connects stages — extending one extends all
- Faster than rack-and-pinion for same motor speed
- Complex rigging, string can break

### Extension Math
\`\`\`
3-stage cascade slide:
Stage 1 length: 24"
Stage 2 length: 22"
Stage 3 length: 20"

Maximum extension = 24 + 22 + 20 = 66"
Starting length (collapsed) = 24"
Net extension = 66 - 24 = 42"

FTC max height: 18" starting, allowed to extend!
FRC frame perimeter rules may limit extension depending on game
\`\`\`

### Rigging for Speed
String cascade doubles the output speed:
\`\`\`
Motor moves Stage 1 up 12"
Stage 2 moves 24" (2× motor travel)
Stage 3 moves 36" (3× motor travel)
\`\`\`

### Common Failure Modes
| Problem | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Slides bind | Misaligned stages | Square up the carriage, add spacers |
| String slips | Wrap not secure | More wraps, add tape, use proper cleat |
| Stages fall | No hard stop | Add physical limit or limit switch |
| Slow extension | Too much friction | Clean channels, add PTFE lubricant |

### Motor Recommendations
- **REV HD Hex 40:1 + string cascade:** Good all-around
- **goBILDA 5202 19.2:1:** Fast, strong
- **REV Core Hex 72:1:** Very strong, slower
