      {id:"ja14",title:"Custom PID Class and Feedforward",est:"30 min",content:`## Building a Reusable PID Controller

Instead of copy-pasting PID code everywhere, build a clean reusable class.

### PIDController Class
\`\`\`java
public class PIDController {
    private double Kp, Ki, Kd, Kf;
    private double integralSum = 0;
    private double lastError   = 0;
    private double lastTime    = 0;
    private double integralMax = 1.0; // Anti-windup limit

    public PIDController(double Kp, double Ki, double Kd, double Kf) {
        this.Kp = Kp; this.Ki = Ki; this.Kd = Kd; this.Kf = Kf;
        lastTime = System.currentTimeMillis() / 1000.0;
    }

    public double calculate(double target, double measured) {
        double now = System.currentTimeMillis() / 1000.0;
        double dt  = now - lastTime;
        if (dt <= 0) dt = 0.02; // Safety: prevent divide-by-zero

        double error      = target - measured;
        integralSum      += error * dt;
        // Anti-windup: clamp integral
        integralSum       = Math.max(-integralMax, Math.min(integralMax, integralSum));
        double derivative = (error - lastError) / dt;

        lastError = error;
        lastTime  = now;

        return Kp*error + Ki*integralSum + Kd*derivative + Kf*Math.signum(target);
    }

    public void reset() { integralSum = 0; lastError = 0; }
    
    // Live tuning setters
    public void setKp(double kp) { Kp = kp; }
    public void setKi(double ki) { Ki = ki; }
    public void setKd(double kd) { Kd = kd; }
}
\`\`\`

### Using the Controller
\`\`\`java
// In OpMode:
PIDController liftPID = new PIDController(0.008, 0.0001, 0.0003, 0.05);
PIDController turnPID = new PIDController(0.015, 0, 0.001, 0);

// Lift control
int liftTarget = 1500; // ticks
double liftPower = liftPID.calculate(liftTarget, lift.getCurrentPosition());
liftPower = Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, liftPower)); // Clamp
lift.setPower(liftPower);

// Turn control
double targetHeading = 90.0;
double currentHeading = imu.getRobotYawPitchRollAngles().getYaw(AngleUnit.DEGREES);
double turnPower = turnPID.calculate(targetHeading, currentHeading);
\`\`\`

### Anti-Windup
Without anti-windup, the integral accumulates infinitely when the motor is at a limit, causing overshoot when it's finally free to move. Clamping integralSum to [-1, 1] prevents this.

### Live Tuning via Telemetry
\`\`\`java
// Change gains mid-match for testing
if (gamepad2.dpad_up)   liftPID.setKp(liftPID.Kp + 0.001);
if (gamepad2.dpad_down) liftPID.setKp(liftPID.Kp - 0.001);
telemetry.addData("Kp", liftPID.Kp);
\`\`\`
