      {id:"sa10",title:"Data-Driven Strategy at Events",est:"25 min",content:`## Using Data to Win

Teams that use data systematically outperform equally skilled teams that rely on gut feelings.

### Build Your Data Pipeline Before the Event
\`\`\`
Pre-event → TBA API pulls team history + average OPR
Quals 1-4 → Scouts calibrate on real match observation  
Quals 5+  → Merge observed data + stats
Alliance selection → Combine: OPR + consistency + climb% + scout notes
\`\`\`

### The Five Metrics That Matter
| Metric | Why It Matters |
|--------|---------------|
| Avg auto pts | Reliable early pts, often has RP implications |
| Avg teleop cycles | Best predictor of teleop contribution |
| Climb success % | Endgame often determines close matches |
| Consistency (std dev) | A team with σ=5 beats σ=15 in high-stakes matches |
| Penalty rate | Penalties directly give opponent points |

### When Stats Lie
**Small sample**: 2-match OPR is meaningless — need ≥ 5 matches
**Opponent quality**: A team scoring 50 against weak alliances may only score 30 vs strong
**Recent changes**: A team that fixed their auto after match 3 will have artificially low stats
**Defense affects OPR**: Teams played against good defenses have lower stats despite being good

### Alliance Selection Data Sheet Format
\`\`\`
Rank | Team | Avg Auto | Avg Cycles | Climb% | σ (std dev) | Scout Note
-----|------|----------|------------|--------|-------------|----------
  1  | 254  |   18.2   |    11.4    |  98%   |     3.1     | Strongest bot
  2  | 1678 |   12.5   |     9.8    |  90%   |     4.2     | Fast cycles
  3  | 971  |    8.0   |     7.2    |  85%   |     6.8     | High variance
\`\`\`

### Live Adjustment During Playoffs
Track alliance scores in real time. At playoff break:
- If losing by >15: increase risk (push harder, attempt harder cycles)
- If winning by >15: play conservatively (protect lead, avoid penalties)
- If within 10: execute the plan exactly as practiced
