    Math.max(
        Math.max(Math.abs(fl), Math.abs(fr)),
        Math.max(Math.abs(bl), Math.abs(br))
    )
);

fl /= maxPower;
fr /= maxPower;
bl /= maxPower;
br /= maxPower;`,explanation:"Without normalization, a motor power of 1.4 would be clipped to 1.0, changing the ratio between wheels and making the robot drift. Dividing by the largest absolute value scales the whole set down while preserving the direction ratios."},
