          {type:"math",label:"Trapezoidal Profile",code:`// Trapezoidal velocity profile
// Three phases: ramp up, cruise, ramp down
double maxVelocity    = 0.8;  // max power level
double acceleration   = 0.05; // power change per loop
double decelDistance  = 200;  // ticks before target to start slowing

double currentVelocity = 0.0;

// In loop:
double distanceToTarget = Math.abs(target - current);

if (distanceToTarget < decelDistance) {
    // Deceleration phase — ramp down
    double decelFraction = distanceToTarget / decelDistance;
    double decelTarget   = maxVelocity * decelFraction;
    currentVelocity = Math.max(0.15, decelTarget); // min power = 0.15
} else if (currentVelocity < maxVelocity) {
    // Acceleration phase — ramp up
    currentVelocity = Math.min(maxVelocity, currentVelocity + acceleration);
}`,explanation:"The trapezoidal profile has three phases. Acceleration: increase velocity each loop until max. Cruise: hold max velocity. Deceleration: as distance to target shrinks, scale velocity proportionally. Keep a minimum power to avoid stalling."},
