      {id:"ji20",title:"Road Runner Basics",est:"28 min",content:`## Road Runner — Smooth Autonomous Trajectories

Road Runner is a motion planning library used by advanced FTC teams. Instead of writing encoder math by hand, you describe paths geometrically.

### What Road Runner Does
- Generates smooth curves (splines) between waypoints
- Runs velocity + acceleration profiles automatically
- Tracks robot position using odometry
- Handles heading continuously during movement

### Setup (FTC Dashboard + Road Runner)
\`\`\`java
// Build a trajectory
Trajectory traj = drive.trajectoryBuilder(new Pose2d(0, 0, 0))
    .splineTo(new Vector2d(30, 15), Math.toRadians(45))  // Curve to (30,15) facing 45°
    .lineTo(new Vector2d(48, 15))                          // Straight to x=48
    .build();

// Execute the trajectory
drive.followTrajectory(traj);
\`\`\`

### Pose2d — Robot Position and Heading
\`\`\`java
// Pose2d(x, y, heading in radians)
// x: inches right from start
// y: inches forward from start
// heading: radians (0 = facing right, π/2 = facing forward)

Pose2d startPose = new Pose2d(-36, -60, Math.toRadians(90)); // Left alliance start
drive.setPoseEstimate(startPose);
\`\`\`

### Trajectory Sequences (Multiple Segments)
\`\`\`java
TrajectorySequence seq = drive.trajectorySequenceBuilder(startPose)
    .forward(24)
    .turn(Math.toRadians(90))
    .waitSeconds(0.5)     // Pause for mechanism
    .strafeLeft(12)
    .forward(6)
    .addTemporalMarker(2.0, () -> { // At T=2 seconds
        lift.setTargetPosition(1200);
        lift.setMode(RunMode.RUN_TO_POSITION);
        lift.setPower(0.8);
    })
    .build();

drive.followTrajectorySequence(seq);
\`\`\`

### Tuning — The Most Important Step
Road Runner requires tuning several constants before it works:
1. **TICKS_PER_REV** — motor encoder ticks per revolution
2. **MAX_RPM** — motor maximum RPM
3. **WHEEL_RADIUS** — drive wheel radius (inches)
4. **GEAR_RATIO** — drive gearing
5. **TRACK_WIDTH** — distance between left/right wheels (tuned empirically)
6. **kV, kA, kStatic** — motor feedforward constants

Use the **Road Runner Quickstart** repo which includes built-in tuning OpModes.
