      {id:"sb11",title:"Understanding Field Elements",est:"15 min",content:`## Know Your Field

Every FIRST game has unique field elements — goals, game pieces, barriers, charge stations. Learning them thoroughly gives you a huge advantage.

### Why Field Knowledge Matters
- Auto paths depend on exact element positions
- Alliance strategy requires knowing every scoring option
- Defense players need to know where they can and can't go
- Human players must understand their feeding zones

### How to Learn a New Game (Kickoff Day)
**First 30 minutes:**
1. Read the Game Manual overview (Section 1-3)
2. Watch the kickoff reveal animation twice
3. Write down every scoring opportunity and its point value

**Next 2 hours:**
4. Study the field layout diagram
5. Walk through every scoring zone mentally
6. Calculate maximum theoretical score (defines the "ceiling")

**Days 2-7:**
7. Watch reveal videos from top teams
8. Attend or watch Q&A sessions
9. Play the field at kickoff events if available

### Maximum Score Analysis
\`\`\`
