// It owns hardware and exposes methods to use it

public class ShooterSubsystem extends SubsystemBase {
    private final CANSparkMax motor = 
        new CANSparkMax(1, MotorType.kBrushless);
    private final RelativeEncoder encoder = motor.getEncoder();

    // Called repeatedly when robot is active
    @Override
    public void periodic() {
        // Log current speed every loop
        SmartDashboard.putNumber("Shooter RPM", encoder.getVelocity());
    }

    // Public methods for Commands to call
    public void spinUp(double rpm) { 
        motor.set(rpm / 5600.0);  // Normalize to [-1,1]
    }
    public void stop() { motor.set(0); }
    public double getRPM() { return encoder.getVelocity(); }
}`,explanation:"The Subsystem owns hardware. No other code touches that hardware directly — everything goes through the Subsystem's public methods. This prevents two commands from fighting over the same motor, which was a major source of bugs in older code."},
          {type:"action",label:"Command Class",code:`// A Command describes what to DO with a Subsystem
// Commands have 4 phases: initialize, execute, end, isFinished

public class SpinUpCommand extends Command {
    private final ShooterSubsystem shooter;
    private final double targetRPM;

    public SpinUpCommand(ShooterSubsystem shooter, double rpm) {
        this.shooter   = shooter;
        this.targetRPM = rpm;
        // Tell scheduler which subsystem this needs
        addRequirements(shooter);
    }

    @Override public void initialize() { shooter.spinUp(targetRPM); }
    @Override public void execute()    { /* Monitor RPM */ }
    @Override public void end(boolean interrupted) { shooter.stop(); }
    @Override public boolean isFinished() {
        return Math.abs(shooter.getRPM() - targetRPM) < 50;
    }
}`,explanation:"addRequirements(shooter) is the key — it tells the Command Scheduler that this command exclusively uses the shooter. If another command also requires the shooter, the scheduler cancels the old one. No more accidental simultaneous motor commands!"},
          {type:"control",label:"Button Binding",code:`// In RobotContainer.java — the 'wiring' class
