      {id:"ji21",title:"Command-Based Programming (FTC)",est:"28 min",content:`## Command-Based Architecture for Complex Robots

Command-based is the professional way to organize complex FTC code — used by top teams worldwide.

### The Core Concepts
- **Subsystem**: A hardware group (drive, arm, intake) with state and actions
- **Command**: An action to perform on one or more subsystems
- **Scheduler**: Runs commands each loop iteration, handles dependencies

### Subsystem Example
\`\`\`java
public class ArmSubsystem {
    private DcMotor armMotor;
    private int targetPosition = 0;

    public ArmSubsystem(HardwareMap hwMap) {
        armMotor = hwMap.get(DcMotor.class, "arm");
        armMotor.setMode(RunMode.RUN_USING_ENCODER);
    }

    // State methods
    public void setTarget(int ticks) {
        targetPosition = ticks;
        armMotor.setTargetPosition(ticks);
        armMotor.setMode(RunMode.RUN_TO_POSITION);
        armMotor.setPower(0.6);
    }

    public boolean atTarget() {
        return !armMotor.isBusy();
    }

    // Called every loop
    public void periodic() {
        // Could update telemetry, run safety checks, etc.
    }
}
\`\`\`

### Command Example
\`\`\`java
public class ScoreCommand {
    ArmSubsystem arm;
    IntakeSubsystem intake;
    int phase = 0;

    public ScoreCommand(ArmSubsystem arm, IntakeSubsystem intake) {
        this.arm = arm;
        this.intake = intake;
    }

    public void execute() {
        switch (phase) {
            case 0:
                arm.setTarget(ArmSubsystem.HIGH_POS);
                phase = 1; break;
            case 1:
                if (arm.atTarget()) {
                    intake.setPower(-1.0); // Eject
                    phase = 2; break;
                }
            case 2:
                // Wait 0.5s then finish...
        }
    }

    public boolean isFinished() { return phase >= 3; }
}
\`\`\`

### Why Use Command-Based?
| Traditional | Command-Based |
|-------------|--------------|
| One giant OpMode | Separate subsystem files |
| Hard to test parts | Test each subsystem solo |
| Adding features = rewrite | Add command, done |
| Bugs hidden in long code | Bugs isolated to one command |
