      {id:"mb15",title:"Fasteners — Choosing the Right Bolt",est:"15 min",content:`## Bolts, Screws, and Nuts for Robots

Choosing wrong fasteners causes field failures. Here's what every builder needs to know.

### Bolt Size Notation
\`\`\`
M3 × 10mm SHCS
│    │     └── Thread type (Socket Head Cap Screw)
│    └──────── Length in mm  
└───────────── Diameter (metric: M2–M10 for robots)

#10-32 × 1/2" BHCS
│   │    │     └── Button Head Cap Screw
│   │    └──────── Length in inches
│   └───────────── Threads per inch
└───────────────── Size (#4=3.18mm, #10=4.83mm)
\`\`\`

### When to Use Each Head Type
| Head Type | Best For | Tool |
|-----------|----------|------|
| Socket Head Cap (SHCS) | Structural joints, high tension | Hex key (Allen) |
| Button Head (BHCS) | Panels, low-profile areas | Hex key |
| Flat Head (FHCS) | Flush mounting, hinges | Hex key |
| Pan Head | Sheet metal, electronics | Phillips/hex |

### Locking Fasteners
- **Nyloc nut**: Nylon ring grips thread — won't vibrate loose. Use for anything that moves.
- **Thread locker (Loctite Blue/242)**: Drop on thread before assembling. Removable with tools. Use on motors, bearing mounts.
- **Split washer**: Old design, not as reliable as nyloc. Avoid.

### Common Mistakes
- ❌ Using smooth-bore holes (no thread) without a nut — bolt will pull right through
- ❌ Over-torquing aluminum — you'll strip the hole
- ❌ Using steel bolts in aluminum without a washer — galvanic corrosion weakens joint over time
- ❌ Not using nyloc on drivetrain — vibration loosens everything

### FTC/FRC Common Sizes
| Use | FTC | FRC |
|-----|-----|-----|
| Motors | M4 × 8mm | #10-32 × 1/2" |
| Structure | M5 × 12mm | 1/4-20 × 3/4" |
| Electronics | M3 × 8mm | #6-32 × 3/8" |
