      {id:"ma6",title:"Mecanum Kinematics & Field-Centric Drive",est:"30 min",content:`## Mecanum Wheel Mathematics

Mecanum wheels let robots strafe in any direction — but only if the math is right.

### Mecanum Wheel Orientation (FTC Standard)
\`\`\`
    FL (//)   FR (\\\\)
    BL (\\\\)   BR (//)

The roller angle creates 45° force vectors.
\`\`\`

### Inverse Kinematics (Joystick → Wheel Powers)
\`\`\`java
double axial   = -gamepad1.left_stick_y;   // Forward/back
double lateral = gamepad1.left_stick_x;    // Strafe left/right
double yaw     = gamepad1.right_stick_x;   // Rotation

// Mecanum equations
double frontLeft  = axial + lateral + yaw;
double frontRight = axial - lateral - yaw;
double backLeft   = axial - lateral + yaw;
double backRight  = axial + lateral - yaw;

// Normalize to [-1, 1] — don't clip!
double maxMag = Math.max(1.0, Math.max(
    Math.max(Math.abs(frontLeft), Math.abs(frontRight)),
    Math.max(Math.abs(backLeft), Math.abs(backRight))));

frontLeft  /= maxMag;
frontRight /= maxMag;
backLeft   /= maxMag;
backRight  /= maxMag;
\`\`\`

### Field-Centric Control
\`\`\`java
// Rotate joystick vector by robot heading
// So "forward" always means field-forward, not robot-forward
double heading = imu.getRobotYawPitchRollAngles().getYaw(AngleUnit.DEGREES);
double rad = Math.toRadians(heading);

// Rotate the lateral/axial vector
double rotLateral = lateral * Math.cos(rad) - axial * Math.sin(rad);
double rotAxial   = lateral * Math.sin(rad) + axial * Math.cos(rad);

// Then apply mecanum equations with rotated inputs
double frontLeft  = rotAxial + rotLateral + yaw;
// ... same as before
\`\`\`

### Tuning Checklist
1. Verify all 4 wheels spin forward when setPower(+0.5) is called
2. Test strafe — robot should move sideways without turning
3. Test rotation — robot spins in place
4. Enable field-centric, verify "forward" on joystick = field forward
5. Test diagonal movement — should be smooth and straight
