      {id:"jaN1",title:"Command-Based Programming (FRC WPILib)",est:"32 min",content:`## Command-Based Architecture

Command-based programming is WPILib's recommended framework for FRC robots. It separates **what the robot can do** (Subsystems) from **when to do it** (Commands).

### Core Concepts
\`\`\`
Subsystem = A robot mechanism (drivetrain, shooter, intake)
Command   = An action that uses one or more subsystems
Trigger   = Something that causes a command to run
Scheduler = Runs all active commands, handles conflicts
\`\`\`

### Creating a Subsystem
\`\`\`java
public class ShooterSubsystem extends SubsystemBase {
    private final CANSparkMax flywheelMotor;
    private final RelativeEncoder encoder;
    private final PIDController pid;
    private double targetRPM = 0;

    public ShooterSubsystem() {
        flywheelMotor = new CANSparkMax(5, MotorType.kBrushless);
        encoder = flywheelMotor.getEncoder();
        pid = new PIDController(0.0002, 0.0001, 0);
    }

    public void setTargetRPM(double rpm) { targetRPM = rpm; }
    public double getRPM() { return encoder.getVelocity(); }
    public boolean atTarget() { return Math.abs(getRPM()-targetRPM) < 50; }

    @Override
    public void periodic() {
        // periodic() runs every loop — like loop() for subsystems
        double output = pid.calculate(getRPM(), targetRPM);
        flywheelMotor.set(output);
        SmartDashboard.putNumber("Shooter RPM", getRPM());
    }
}
\`\`\`

### Creating Commands
\`\`\`java
// InstantCommand — runs once immediately
new InstantCommand(() -> shooter.setTargetRPM(3000), shooter);

// RunCommand — runs every loop until interrupted
new RunCommand(() -> {
    shooter.setTargetRPM(3000);
}, shooter);

// Full command class for complex logic:
public class SpinUpCommand extends Command {
    private final ShooterSubsystem shooter;
    private final double targetRPM;

    public SpinUpCommand(ShooterSubsystem shooter, double rpm) {
        this.shooter = shooter;
        this.targetRPM = rpm;
        addRequirements(shooter); // Declares ownership
    }

    @Override public void initialize() { shooter.setTargetRPM(targetRPM); }
    @Override public boolean isFinished() { return shooter.atTarget(); }
    @Override public void end(boolean interrupted) {
        if (interrupted) shooter.setTargetRPM(0);
    }
}
\`\`\`

### Button Bindings in RobotContainer
\`\`\`java
// RobotContainer.java — bind buttons to commands
JoystickButton shootButton = new JoystickButton(gamepad, 1);

// While held: spin up. When released: stop.
shootButton.whileTrue(new SpinUpCommand(shooter, 3500));

// On press only:
shootButton.onTrue(new InstantCommand(()->intake.toggle()));

// Composed commands:
shootButton.onTrue(
    new SpinUpCommand(shooter, 3500)
        .andThen(new FeedCommand(feeder, 0.5))
        .withTimeout(2.0)
);
\`\`\`
