      {id:"sbN1",title:"Reading the Game Manual Like a Pro",est:"18 min",content:`## Game Manual Deep Dive

The game manual is your rulebook, scoring guide, and strategy bible all in one. Most teams don't read it carefully enough.

### Manual Structure (FRC/FTC)
\`\`\`
Section 1: Introduction — season theme, overview
Section 2: Arena — field dimensions, elements
Section 3: The Game — scoring, period rules
Section 4: The Robot — build rules, allowed materials
Section 5: Tournament — event structure, ranking
Section 6: Inspection — what referees check
Appendices — forms, legal parts lists, Q&A
\`\`\`

### First Read: 30-Minute Strategy Sprint
Do this within 24 hours of kickoff:

**Step 1 — Scoring:** Read Section 3 end-to-end. Circle every point value. Calculate maximum possible score.

**Step 2 — Ranking:** Find what earns Ranking Points. These shape your qualification strategy.

**Step 3 — Red flags:** Note any rules that could disqualify you or give opponents RP.

**Step 4 — Constraints:** What robot rules most limit your design? Height? Weight? Extension?

### Annotated Reading Example
\`\`\`
Rule G401: "Robots may not extend beyond their FRAME PERIMETER..."
↳ Mark: Maximum extension = ___ inches
