      {id:"eiN1",title:"Sensor Fusion — Combining Multiple Sensors",est:"24 min",content:`## Sensor Fusion: Better Together

No single sensor is perfect. Combining multiple sensors gives you more reliable measurements than any one alone.

### Why Fuse Sensors?
\`\`\`
IMU (gyro) alone:
  ✅ Fast, no drift over short time
  ❌ Drifts over long matches, affected by vibration

Odometry (encoders) alone:
  ✅ Accurate for straight movement
  ❌ Wheel slip causes drift in turns

Vision (camera) alone:
  ✅ Absolute position from field markers
  ❌ Can lose target, slow update rate

FUSED: IMU + Encoders + Vision = 
  Continuous tracking + drift correction + absolute reset
\`\`\`

### Dead Reckoning + IMU Correction
\`\`\`java
// Track position using encoders
double x = 0, y = 0;

// Each loop:
double deltaLeft = leftEncoder.getPositionInches();
double deltaRight = rightEncoder.getPositionInches();
double avgDelta = (deltaLeft + deltaRight) / 2.0;

// Use IMU heading (more reliable than encoder turning)
double heading = imu.getRobotYawPitchRollAngles()
                    .getYaw(AngleUnit.RADIANS);

// Update position using heading for direction
x += avgDelta * Math.cos(heading);
y += avgDelta * Math.sin(heading);
\`\`\`

### Vision Reset (AprilTag Correction)
\`\`\`java
// When AprilTag detected: trust vision over dead reckoning
if (!aprilTagDetections.isEmpty()) {
    AprilTagDetection det = aprilTagDetections.get(0);
    if (det.ftcPose.range < 36) { // Only trust close readings
        // Reset estimated position to vision measurement
        // (Much more accurate than accumulated odometry error)
        poseX = fieldPoseFromTag(det);
        poseY = fieldPoseFromTag(det);
    }
}
\`\`\`

### Simple Complementary Filter
\`\`\`java
// Complementary filter: trust gyro for fast changes,
// trust accelerometer for slow changes
// alpha = 0.98 means 98% gyro, 2% accel
double alpha = 0.98;
fusedAngle = alpha * (fusedAngle + gyroRate * dt)
           + (1-alpha) * accelAngle;
\`\`\`

### When to Use Each
- **Short auto (< 5 sec):** Dead reckoning + IMU usually sufficient
- **Long auto or complex paths:** Add vision resets at scoring positions
- **Teleop field-centric:** IMU only (fast, simple, accurate enough)
