          <div style={{background:"#fff",borderRadius:12,padding:16,border:"1px solid #e2e8f0",fontSize:13,color:"#6b7280",lineHeight:1.7}}>
            <strong>Tips:</strong> For drive trains, target 12–16 ft/s. For arms/lifts, prioritize torque over speed. A higher gear ratio = more torque, lower speed. The 80% operating speed is a common approximation for loaded operation.
